name: Pastor Rick & Heather Neufeld
bio:
As of August 2016 Pastor Rick Neufeld, along with his wife Heather and children Tendai and Ryan, has joined us as full time Senior Pastor here at Abundant Life Fellowship. Prior to this they were full time missionaries with SAM Ministries in Mozambique for the past 10 years, where they were involved in training Pastors as well as working with the orphan sponsorship program. Pastor Rick and Heather also have experience with both youth and children ministries as they held positions of Youth Pastor and Bible Camp Directors in the past.

They have a heart of compassion for the lost as well as a desire to teach and disciple the followers of Jesus. We are blessed as a congregation to have them and are excited to see God use them to spur us on and disciple us as a family of believers in the years to come!

name: Lorne & Wanda Bell
bio:
Welcome to Lorne and Wanda Bell as they join the Pastoral team as our Discipleship Pastor couple! Lorne comes to us with a wealth of experience in teaching and training which he will use to further discipleship training at GALF. He has a true heart for the Church and desires all to have a close relationship with Christ as well as with fellow believers.

Wanda feels a true calling to help both girls and women see their worth and potential in Jesus Christ. She has a desire to connect women within the body to support one another and grow in Christ.

We are excited to have them join the team and look forward to great things ahead!
